<paragraph blockId="17.[132,775,1922,2026]" lastBlockId="17.[813,1456,215,345]" pageId="17" pageNumber="498">
<collectionCode box="[132,229,1923,1947]" pageId="17" pageNumber="498">ORIGINAL</collectionCode>
DATA. — Four individuals of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Matschie" authorityYear="1894" box="[530,722,1922,1946]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Scotonycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="498" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="zenkeri">
<emphasis box="[530,722,1922,1946]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="498">Scotonycteris zenkeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were netted in an undisturbed lowland forest of mount 
<collectingCountry box="[618,722,1949,1973]" name="Cameroon" pageId="17" pageNumber="498">Cameroon</collectingCountry>
at an altitude of 
<quantity box="[240,305,1975,1999]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.3" pageId="17" pageNumber="498" unit="m" value="630.0">630 m</quantity>
a.s.l (
<tableCitation box="[364,437,1975,1999]" captionStart="TABLE" captionStartId="6.[134,145,230,248]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="TABLE 1. — Sampling stations, habitat sampled and species captured during our field surveys (2016-2018). Abbreviations: A, above slow-flowing steam, B, cultivated farm; C, fallow farmland; D, beside fruiting tree; E, cleared farmland; F, understory of Primary forest; G, ecotone forest/alpine grassland, H, cave; I, gap between trees; J, forest fragment; K, waterhole." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF4C665DD54639431C8FFF45FDEA411C" pageId="17" pageNumber="498" tableUuid="DF4C665DD54639431C8FFF45FDEA411C">Table 1</tableCitation>
). This species had previously been recorded in the lowland forest of Mount 
<collectingCountry box="[534,638,2002,2026]" name="Cameroon" pageId="17" pageNumber="498">Cameroon</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Eisentraut" box="[675,879,215,2025]" firstAuthor="Eisentraut" pageId="17" pageNumber="498" refId="ref25058" refString="EISENTRAUT M. 1963. - Die Wirbeltiere des Kamerungebirges. Verlag Paul Parey, Hamburg, 353 p." type="book" year="1963">Eisentraut (1963)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hayman &amp; Hill" box="[889,1111,215,239]" firstAuthor="Hayman" pageId="17" pageNumber="498" refId="ref27070" refString="HAYMAN R. W. &amp; HILL J. E. 1971. - Order Chiroptera. in MEESTER J &amp; SETZER, H W. (eds), The mammals of Africa. An identification manual. Part 2, Smithsonian Institution Press. Washington, D. C, 73 p." type="book" year="1971">Hayman &amp; Hill (1971)</bibRefCitation>
, and by 
<bibRefCitation author="Fedden &amp; MacLeod" box="[1188,1450,215,239]" firstAuthor="Fedden" pageId="17" pageNumber="498" pagination="175 - 195" refId="ref25479" refString="FEDDEN M. O. &amp; MACLEOD H. L. 1986. - Bat research in western Cameroon in S. N. STUART (ed.), Conservation of Cameroon montane forest. Report of the ICBP Cameroon Montane Forest Survey November 1983 - April 1984. International Council for Bird Preservation, Cambridge: 175 - 195." type="book chapter" year="1986">Fedden &amp; MacLeod (1986)</bibRefCitation>
, who mist-netted three individuals in a primary undisturbed forest. At Mount Nimba it was recorded at altitudes between 
<quantity box="[1361,1427,268,292]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="498" unit="m" value="500.0">500 m</quantity>
to 
<quantity box="[813,878,294,318]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="498" unit="m" value="600.0">600 m</quantity>
a.s.l. by 
<bibRefCitation author="Coe" box="[968,1083,294,318]" firstAuthor="Coe" pageId="17" pageNumber="498" pagination="523 - 587" refId="ref24428" refString="COE M. J. 1975. - Mammalian ecological studies on Mount Nimba, Liberia. Mammalia 39: 523 - 587. https: // doi. org / 10.1515 / mamm. 1975.39.4.523" type="journal article" year="1975">Coe (1975)</bibRefCitation>
and at altitude below 
<quantity box="[1307,1373,294,318]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="498" unit="m" value="800.0">800 m</quantity>
a.s.l. by 
<bibRefCitation author="Wolton" box="[813,1014,321,345]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Wolton" pageId="17" pageNumber="498" pagination="419 - 448" refId="ref30317" refString="WOLTON R. J., ARAK P. A., GODFRAY H. J., &amp; WILSON R. P. 1982. - Ecological and behavioural studies of the Megachiroptera at Mount Nimba, Liberia, with notes on Microchiroptera. Mammalia 46: 419 - 448." type="journal article" year="1982">
Wolton 
<emphasis box="[893,940,321,345]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="498">et al.</emphasis>
(1982)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="498" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="17.[813,1456,372,529]" pageId="17" pageNumber="498">
DIAGNOSIS. — The four specimens display the characteristic brown head with prominent white spots on the forehead between nostrils and the eyes, small white spots at the posterior corner of each eye, and lips fringed with white (
<figureCitation box="[1102,1161,451,476]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="9.[486,497,1494,1512]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,215,1452]" captionTargetId="figure-289@9.[132,1455,215,1452]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIG. 3. — Eidolon helvum (Kerr, 1792). Photo: © Aaron Manga Mongombe." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4060049" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4060049/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="498">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). The external measurements (
<tableCitation box="[821,889,478,502]" captionStart="TABLE" captionStartId="12.[134,145,220,238]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="TABLE 3. — External measurements of adult bats captured on Mount Cameroon. Measurements are given as mean ± standard deviation and range." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF4C665DD54C39491C8FFF7FFAB440D7" pageId="17" pageNumber="498" tableUuid="DF4C665DD54C39491C8FFF7FFAB440D7">Table 3</tableCitation>
), and description generally agree with those of 
<bibRefCitation author="Fahr" box="[1324,1450,478,502]" firstAuthor="Fahr" pageId="17" pageNumber="498" pagination="297 - 299" refId="ref25226" refString="FAHR J. 2013 b. - Scotonycteris zenkeri. Zenker's Fruit Bat, in D. C. D. HAPPOLD, J. KINGDON &amp; T. BUTYNSKI (eds), The mammals of Africa, Volume IV: hedgehogs, shrews and bats. Bloomsbury Publishing, London: 297 - 299. http: // doi. org / 10.5040 / 9781472926944.0190" type="book chapter" year="2013" yearSuffix="b">Fahr (2013b)</bibRefCitation>
, and Nigerian specimens described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Happold" box="[1181,1343,504,529]" firstAuthor="Happold" pageId="17" pageNumber="498" refId="ref25900" refString="HAPPOLD D. C. D. 1987. - The mammals of Nigeria. Clarendon Press. Oxford, 402 p. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0030605300027708" type="book" year="1987">Happold (1987)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="498" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="17.[813,1455,556,765]" pageId="17" pageNumber="498">
HABITATS AND DISTRIBUTION. — This species has a limited distribution in Central Africa, centered on 
<collectingCountry box="[1210,1314,582,606]" name="Cameroon" pageId="17" pageNumber="498">Cameroon</collectingCountry>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Hassanin" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Hassanin" pageId="17" pageNumber="498" pagination="197 - 211" refId="ref26861" refString="HASSANIN A., KHOUIDER S., GEMBU G. C., GOODMAN S. M., KADJO B., NESI N., POURRUT X., NAKOUNE E. &amp; BONILLO C. 2015. - The comparative phylogeography of fruit bats of the tribe Scotonycterini (Chiroptera, Pteropodidae) reveals cryptic species diversity related to African Pleistocene forest refugia. Comptes Rendus Biologies 338 (3): 197 - 211. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. crvi. 2014.12.003" type="journal article" year="2015">
Hassanin 
<emphasis box="[813,861,609,633]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="498">et al.</emphasis>
2015
</bibRefCitation>
). According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Bergmans" box="[1075,1246,609,633]" firstAuthor="Bergmans" pageId="17" pageNumber="498" pagination="111 - 177" refId="ref24090" refString="BERGMANS W. 1990. - Taxonomy and biogeography of African fruit bats (Mammalia, Megachiroptera). 3. The genera Scotonycteris Matschie, 1894, Casinycteris Thomas, 1910, Pteropus Brisson, 1762, and Eidolon Rafinesque, 1815. Beaufortia 40: 111 - 177. https: // repository. naturalis. nl / pub / 504806" type="journal article" year="1990">Bergmans (1990)</bibRefCitation>
, this species inhabits tropical lowland and montane forest where it lives in the lower strata of the forest about 
<quantity box="[1061,1101,662,686]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="498" unit="m" value="3.0">3 m</quantity>
above the ground (
<bibRefCitation author="Happold" box="[1295,1441,662,686]" firstAuthor="Happold" pageId="17" pageNumber="498" refId="ref25900" refString="HAPPOLD D. C. D. 1987. - The mammals of Nigeria. Clarendon Press. Oxford, 402 p. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0030605300027708" type="book" year="1987">Happold 1987</bibRefCitation>
); it roosts singly in trees or bushes (
<bibRefCitation author="Happold" box="[1133,1277,688,712]" firstAuthor="Happold" pageId="17" pageNumber="498" refId="ref25900" refString="HAPPOLD D. C. D. 1987. - The mammals of Nigeria. Clarendon Press. Oxford, 402 p. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0030605300027708" type="book" year="1987">Happold 1987</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Fahr" box="[1288,1400,688,712]" firstAuthor="Fahr" pageId="17" pageNumber="498" pagination="297 - 299" refId="ref25226" refString="FAHR J. 2013 b. - Scotonycteris zenkeri. Zenker's Fruit Bat, in D. C. D. HAPPOLD, J. KINGDON &amp; T. BUTYNSKI (eds), The mammals of Africa, Volume IV: hedgehogs, shrews and bats. Bloomsbury Publishing, London: 297 - 299. http: // doi. org / 10.5040 / 9781472926944.0190" type="book chapter" year="2013" yearSuffix="b">Fahr 2013b</bibRefCitation>
). It is threatened by habitat loss through deforestation and the conversion of primary forest to agricultural use.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="498" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[813,1455,792,896]" pageId="17" pageNumber="498">
REMARK. — Based on molecular analyses, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hassanin" box="[1235,1455,792,817]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Hassanin" pageId="17" pageNumber="498" pagination="197 - 211" refId="ref26861" refString="HASSANIN A., KHOUIDER S., GEMBU G. C., GOODMAN S. M., KADJO B., NESI N., POURRUT X., NAKOUNE E. &amp; BONILLO C. 2015. - The comparative phylogeography of fruit bats of the tribe Scotonycterini (Chiroptera, Pteropodidae) reveals cryptic species diversity related to African Pleistocene forest refugia. Comptes Rendus Biologies 338 (3): 197 - 211. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. crvi. 2014.12.003" type="journal article" year="2015">
Hassanin 
<emphasis box="[1333,1381,792,816]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="498">et al.</emphasis>
(2015)
</bibRefCitation>
split 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Matschie" authorityYear="1894" box="[859,1048,819,843]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Scotonycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="498" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="zenkeri">
<emphasis box="[859,1048,819,843]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="498">Scotonycteris zenkeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
into three species: 
<taxonomicName box="[1228,1455,819,843]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Scotonycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="498" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="occidentalis">
<emphasis box="[1228,1455,819,843]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="498">Scotonycteris occidentalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Upper 
<collectingCountry box="[939,1010,845,869]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="17" pageNumber="498">Guinea</collectingCountry>
Region of West Africa, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Matschie" authorityYear="1894" box="[1233,1323,845,869]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Scotonycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="498" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="zenkeri">
<emphasis box="[1233,1323,845,869]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="498">S. zenkeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[1352,1455,845,869]" name="Cameroon" pageId="17" pageNumber="498">Cameroon</collectingCountry>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hassanin, Khouider, Gembu, Goodman, Kadjo, Nesi, Pourrut, Nakoune &amp; Bonillo" authorityYear="2015" box="[855,975,872,896]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Scotonycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="498" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bergmansi">
<emphasis box="[855,975,872,896]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="498">S. bergmansi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Central Africa.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
